<!doctype html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T006 Digital Setup Packet</title><style>@page{margin:.6in}body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.45;color:#111827;max-width:8.1in;margin:0 auto;background:#fff}h1{background:#1f2937;color:#fff;padding:16px 18px;border-radius:10px;font-size:22pt;margin:0 0 14px}h2{color:#0f172a;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px;margin:18px 0 8px;font-size:15pt}p{margin:8px 0 12px}ul{margin:8px 0 14px 24px}li{margin:4px 0}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;table-layout:fixed;margin:10px 0 16px}th,td{border:1px solid #b7c3d0;padding:8px 9px;vertical-align:top;word-wrap:break-word}th{background:#dbeafe;color:#0f172a;text-align:left}.meta{background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #dbe3ec;border-radius:10px;padding:10px 12px}.visual{text-align:center;margin:12px 0 16px}.visual img{width:100%;max-width:7.15in;height:auto;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:10px}.note{background:#eff6ff;border-left:6px solid #0ea5e9;padding:10px 12px;margin:12px 0 16px;border-radius:6px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Digital Setup Packet</h1><p class="meta"><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T006<br><b>Scenario:</b> Services, photos, and messages to one request path</p><div class="visual"><img src="../assets/sample-digital-setup-proof.svg" alt="Digital setup visual"></div><h2>Customer input</h2><ul><li>Service descriptions, coverage area, photos, and current contact method.</li><li>Problem: customers ask questions in too many places and details get missed.</li><li>Goal: one clean path from page to form to tracker to reply.</li></ul><h2>Setup map</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:22%"><col style="width:40%"><col style="width:38%"></colgroup><tr><th>Step</th><th>Built output</th><th>Customer result</th></tr><tr><td>Page</td><td>Headline, service sections, proof, FAQ, CTA.</td><td>Visitor understands what to request.</td></tr><tr><td>Form</td><td>Fields for service, goal, files, timing, budget.</td><td>Owner gets usable info first time.</td></tr><tr><td>Tracker</td><td>Status, next action, due date, package, amount.</td><td>No request gets lost.</td></tr><tr><td>Reply</td><td>Confirmation and missing-info templates.</td><td>Faster first response.</td></tr></table><h2>Recommended first build</h2><div class="note">Start with one page, one request form, one lead tracker, and two email templates before adding more tools.</div></body></html>